<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFBFFE5E1FD0319FD0AFC9E" authority="Staudinger, 1892" authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1892" box="[199,681,834,861]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="phoebe" variety="saturata">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E1FD0319FE7CFC9E" bold="true" box="[199,479,834,861]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">M. phoebe var. saturata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFBFFE5E0D30319FD0AFC9E" author="Staudinger, O." box="[489,681,835,861]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="300 - 393" refId="ref11225" refString="Staudinger, O. (1892) Lepidopteren des Kentei-Gebirges. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, Iris, 5, 300 - 393." type="journal article" year="1892">Staudinger, 1892</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1BD8652DFFFBFFE5E3890319FE16FB9A" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="537D36A6FFFBFFE5E3890319FE16FB9A" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
[TL: Kentai Mountains, 
<collectingCountry id="2BD57636FFFBFFE5E2F10318FB98FC9E" box="[971,1083,834,861]" name="Mongolia" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
] A large and brightly coloured form typical of ‘mountain forms’ (
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFBFFE5E326033DFD50FC42" author="Higgins, L. G." box="[540,755,871,897]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="175 - 365" refId="ref9372" refString="Higgins, L. G. (1941) An illustrated catalogue of the Palearctic Melitaea (Lep. Rhopalocera). Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 91, 175 - 365. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1941. tb 01045. x" type="journal article" year="1941">Higgins 1941: 342</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFBFFE5E23D033DFBC4FC42" author="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G." box="[775,1127,871,897]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" refId="ref11693" refString="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G. (2014) The genus Melitaea Fabricius, 1807 (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae, Nymphalinae) Taxonomy and systematics with special reference to the male genitalia. Tshikolovets publications, Pardubice, Czech Republic, 360 pp." type="book" year="2014">Van Oorschot &amp; Coutsis (2014</bibRefCitation>
: plate 12, fig. 25) figured a brightly coloured male 
<typeStatus id="8C798804FFFBFFE5E0A603D1FE50FC66" box="[412,499,907,933]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">syntype</typeStatus>
from the Staudinger collection in Zoologisches Museum der Humboldt Universität, Berlin. Both authors synonymised this 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFBFFE5E37203F5FD6DFC0A" box="[584,718,943,969]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" rank="variety" variety="with">variety with</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFBFFE5E3E903F5FCEAFC0A" baseAuthorityName="Denis &amp; Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[723,841,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E3E903F5FCEAFC0A" box="[723,841,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as did 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFBFFE5E2A703F5FB7DFC0A" author="Russell, PJ &amp; Tennent, W. J." box="[925,1246,942,969]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="27 - 56" refId="ref10922" refString="Russell, PJ. C. &amp; Tennent, W. J. (2016) A synonymic list of names associated with western Palaearctic Melitaea phoebe (Denis &amp; Schiffermuller, 1775) species group taxa M. phoebe; M. punica Oberthur, 1876; M. ornata Christoph, 1893) (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae). Nota Lepidopterologica, 39 (1), 27 - 56. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / nl. 39.5929" type="journal article" year="2016">Russell &amp; Tennent (2016: 53</bibRefCitation>
, note 80). On the internet www.funet.fi (accessed 
<date id="277C1066FFFBFFE5E0C60389FDDFFC2D" box="[508,636,979,1006]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="2020-10-26">26.10.2020</date>
) has a photograph (© Kosterin) of the underside of a female(?), from the Iskitim District, Novosibirst Province, Western Siberia, 
<collectingCountry id="2BD57636FFFBFFE5E23903ADFC79FBD2" box="[771,986,1015,1041]" name="Russia" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Russian Federation</collectingCountry>
on 
<date id="277C1066FFFBFFE5E53803ADFB00FBD2" box="[1026,1187,1015,1041]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="1997-06-21">
21 
<superScript id="A4B79BEEFFFBFFE5E52403ADFB8AFBC6" attach="left" box="[1054,1065,1015,1029]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">st</superScript>
June 1997
</date>
; this shows clearly the wing markings and antennae distinctive of 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFBFFE5E3410441FD52FBF6" baseAuthorityName="Denis &amp; Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[635,753,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E3410441FD52FBF6" box="[635,753,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than of 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFBFFE5E2AD0441FBA4FBF7" authorityName="Christoph" authorityYear="1893" box="[919,1031,1051,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E2AD0441FBA4FBF7" box="[919,1031,1051,1076]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">M. ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We confirm that the name 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E4050441FA3FFBF7" box="[1343,1436,1051,1076]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">saturata</emphasis>
is referable to 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFBFFE5E0020465FE0DFB9A" baseAuthorityName="Denis &amp; Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[312,430,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E0020465FE0DFB9A" box="[312,430,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
